<br>
But at the end of the day. You and I have no idea what choices we make are going to make us a better, or worse person. I cannot say for definite that if you condition your child to think something, it will make her better or worse. You can't say for definite that doing the opposite will either. <br>
<br>
That means, in terms of growth, and learning, conditioning doesn't matter, all it does is limits a persons choices, which in the end, is limiting their freedom. Which, in my opinion, is a bad thing.<br>
