<br>
Inaccurate and morally unsound information:  &quot;Niggers are ruining our country, kick em out or string em up.&quot;<br>
<br>
You see?  To any human being worth the name, some things are right, and some things are wrong.  Anyone who appears to be human but would actually debate that point, isn't really a human.  They're just fur-challenged, marginally housetrained monkeys.<br>
<br>
Now, I'll grant you that not all cases are as clear-cut as that one, and there are times when a genuine debate might exist.  But I was talking about education, and you'd expect a reasonably ethical class teacher to mention when something was a point of disagreement.<br>
<br>
Accurate and morally sound:  &quot;Some people think that nuclear power plants are a damaging thing for our country, while others feel that they're the best way forward.&quot;<br>
<br>
Inaccurate and morally unsound:  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Either</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;Nuclear power sucks, let's all go chain ourselves to fences children&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>or</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;Nuclear power's the best, let's go play in the toxic waste&quot;. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=162740">Shadowfrost</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shadowfrostxev>ShadowfrostXev</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www-und.ida.liu.se/~johro897/flags/uk.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>8/6/03 - we will remember</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#330000>(8/19/03 9:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Social Brainwashing</span><hr size=1> Oh yeah, and as for teaching Creationism in schools, that gave me a damn good laugh, so thanks.  I understand that there really are places like that across the pond, but if you just <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>have</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to live in America, what do you expect?<br>
